windows.question:
Which of the following best describes the anomaly detection results within the time series window spanning steps 889 to 915?
A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
C) Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.
options.C: Downward Spike anomaly: Values plunge dramatically in a sudden downward spike.

windows.answer: B) Upward Spike anomaly: There is a sharp upward jump in the measurements.

windows.question:

A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
B) Irregularly Pattern anomaly: The segment shows irregular oscillations without a stable trend.
C) Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

options.A: The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
options.B: Irregularly Pattern anomaly: The segment shows irregular oscillations without a stable trend.
options.C: Downward Convex anomaly: Values form a downward convex curve that decreases more sharply than the surrounding trend.

windows.answer: A) The time series values evolve smoothly without sudden spikes, drops, or irregular patterns.
